=== Clash95 continuity campaign-route extra v5 (redraw second-instruction hook) ===
Harness-only continuity probe for a 600s-plus campaign route on the hidden
desktop. Prior findings: the world-map poll 0040B0C3 fires once per call,
Render_Present 00460EA0 never fires on the map path, and the base template
owns bp 00406FA0 with its definition composed after any extra. The per
frame steady state therefore hooks 00406FA1 - the second instruction of
the redraw function, push edx - which fires every redraw frame with no
breakpoint conflict. First poll hit latches the base dump flag t7 and
snapshots saveGame slot 11. Every 0x1000 redraw hits force the engine
next-player routine 0040AA60 for real multi-day turn processing, with
eax edx ecx stashed and restored around every forced call. After 0n39040
ticks from KUSER_SHARED_DATA 7ffe0320 - about 610 seconds at the standard
64Hz tick - snapshot saveGame slot 12, release t7 and set t13 to 4, and
the base template dump ends the run. Duration independently verifiable
from 11.dat and 12.dat file timestamps.
